column5: Solid specimen for your first    Congrats
Nice! Congrats!
Great fish! Congratultions on the PB
Congrats, great fish, thats one obsession that will be hard on the wallet!
Congrats, beauty fish.  All other fish are bait now

well...after a few years fishing i finally landed a muskie .......went out with a few friends today on lake seymore....looking for bass...we landed a few but it was a very slow day.....i was throwing a chartreuse spinner with no leader,tied to a 50 lbs braid.....and wham all hell broke lose....jose said the whole lake heard me scream!!!....what a rush!!!....new personal best!!!!  he measured 44"....quick photo  and off he went....swam away healthy!!!
Congrats!  What a monster!!
Congrats...now prepare to become obsessed.
Awesome fish! Congrats!
Well done workwear, she's a purty fish indeed !!
Great feeling isn't it? Nice fat Ski. Congrats
WTG on a PB!  That was your 1st?  WOW  Good Job!

thanks guys.......it was a whole new experience....heart pumping..a true adrenalin high....after he swam away....i sat down and had a few smokes to calm down.....after that release i had no intrest in those other little green fish....lol....now im on the hunt to get one of terry's customized 50 dollar bills.....wooohoooo
.. and another one falls to the dark side!!
Peter remember what Ron said lol  Had fun today like always and its 3 to 6 don't forget it's not over till the fat lady but in your case the fat man has song

Congrats for sure.  Now your going to be biting the bullet hard tell your wife your sorry its easier then asking for the $$$ to buy the Leaders,Knipex bolt cutters,long nose pliers, Congrats - nice fish
Great way to get started.   Congrats on such a nice fish.
Sweet fish workwear. Congrats !
That's a good fish...  Was it on bass gear?... If so, that must have been some battle
Wow, congrats, she's a beaut for sure.  Great feeling eh
nice fish man !!! congrats !!!!
Got to imagine that the ol' legs were just a shakin!!! Congrats!!
Nice one, I can't wait to get a musky. I'm hoping to get out to the Kawarthas sometime this summer. Congrats on the PB as well.

Wow, nice! I would like to catch a muskie some day. Some day... I don't even know where I could get one close to me (Lake Temiskaming, maybe? I don't even know), and I would need a whole different setup, I think. Or are they commonly caught in a '68 Sportspal?
Great Muskie - congrats!
Very nice Looking & a Big congrats SBK

thanks everyone for all your comments......yes caught this on a spinner bait without a leader...50lbs braid ....yes i did have shakey legs when i saw his back....new it wasnt a pike...gave me a good fight....but he did swim away after a few pics....and for all that wanna know....IM STILL SMILING!!
